Angelino: &ldquo;Pep killed me and my self-confidence. After my move from PSV back to Manchester City, he had already passed his judgement on me in two games and didn&rsquo;t give me a real chance after that. That&rsquo;s why I was happy to be loaned to Leipzig in the first place...&quot;<br />
<br />
&quot;Now I&rsquo;m a permanent part of the club. One manager [Nagelsmann] gave me confidence, let me play. The other [Guardiola] didn&rsquo;t. At Leipzig, I felt confidence from day one. The club/coach gave me an incredible push. I'm happy to play consistently.&rdquo;

